<subSubSection id="08AE557053260F7B0ECBDEE9E7967F47" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1401B03F7B18F82F69F7E5D2CC540FDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A73B1C56BCD9F4B378E939693D378CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Appears to be related to 
<taxonomicName id="127884C81E568883D6C6F0E5A71EC005" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nationis">
<emphasis id="9D30CC47FA961D9E2A7EB40A1CA5C327" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea nationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but sepals very unequal in size, the corolla tube shorter and all parts glabrous. The placement of this species is provisional.
</paragraph>
